Program: The History Hour
Title: Korea Divided: A Bitter History
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3cswqll
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 17 Jun 2018
From the 1945 division of the peninsula, to the Korean war and the death of Kim II-sung, we have first-hand accounts from the turbulent recent history of North and South Korea. Plus, expert analysis from Dr Owen Miller of SOAS University of London. Photo: As US infantrymen march into the Naktong River region, they pass a line of fleeing refugees during the Korean War (Getty images) Show less